+# Rust standard library port for OS userland
+
+This directory contains the target description, startup object, and linker
+script for building normal Rust programs with this repository's port of `std`.
+The port is pinned to the same Rust commit as `rust-toolchain.toml`; the host
+compiler supplied by rustup is reused, so building the complete Rust compiler
+is not required.
+
+The platform abstraction uses the kernel's user syscall ABI directly:
+
+- `a0 = 0`, `a1 = status`: exit
+- `a0 = 1`, `a1 = fd`, `a2 = buffer`, `a3 = length`: write
+- `a0 = 2`, `a1 = fd`, `a2 = buffer`, `a3 = length`: read
+- `a0 = 3`, `a1 = path`, `a2 = length`: open
+- `a0 = 4`, `a1 = fd`: close
+- `a0 = 6`, `a1 = milliseconds`: sleep
+
+Returning syscalls place a status in `a0` and a value in `a1`. A zero status
+denotes success. The startup object initializes `gp`, calls Rust's generated
+`main` entry point, and exits through syscall 0.
+
+## Implemented surface
+
+- `println!`, `eprintln!`, standard input, and the `Read`/`Write` APIs use file
+  descriptors 0, 1, and 2.
+- `Vec`, `String`, maps, and the rest of `alloc` use `dlmalloc` over a 4 MiB
+  zero-filled heap reserved by `os.ld`.
+- `std::fs::File` and helpers such as `std::fs::read_to_string` can read files
+  from the init archive with open/read/close.
+- `std::thread::sleep` uses the millisecond sleep syscall.
+- Single-thread synchronization and thread-local storage work. Creating new OS
+  threads is not supported because the kernel ABI does not expose that yet.
+
+The init archive is read-only, so file creation and mutation are unsupported.
+Seeking, metadata, wall/monotonic clocks, networking, subprocesses, and
+environment mutation also remain unsupported until matching kernel services
+exist.
+
+## Build
+
+From the repository root:
+
+```sh
+make ports-prepare PORTS=rust
+make -C userland/rust-std build ROOTFS_BIN="$PWD/artifacts/rootfs/bin"
+```
+
+The example under `userland/rust-std` is ordinary Rust source (no `no_std`
+attributes). It exercises allocation, formatted output, file reading, and
+sleep. The regular userland build installs it as `/bin/rust-std-demo`.
diff --git a/os/os.ld b/os/os.ld
new file mode 100644
index 00000000..ea787db1
--- /dev/null
+++ b/os/os.ld
@@ -0,0 +1,57 @@
+OUTPUT_ARCH(riscv)
+ENTRY(_start)
+
+PHDRS
+{
+    text PT_LOAD FLAGS(5);
+    rodata PT_LOAD FLAGS(4);
+    data PT_LOAD FLAGS(6);
+}
+
+SECTIONS
+{
+    . = 0x10000;
+
+    .text : ALIGN(0x1000)
+    {
+        KEEP(*(.text._start))
+        *(.text .text.*)
+    } :text
+
+    .rodata : ALIGN(0x1000)
+    {
+        *(.rodata .rodata.*)
+        *(.srodata .srodata.*)
+    } :rodata
+
+    .data : ALIGN(0x1000)
+    {
+        __data_start = .;
+        *(.data .data.*)
+        *(.sdata .sdata.*)
+    } :data
+
+    .bss (NOLOAD) : ALIGN(0x1000)
+    {
+        __bss_start = .;
+        *(.bss .bss.*)
+        *(.sbss .sbss.*)
+        *(COMMON)
+        __bss_end = .;
+    } :data
+
+    .heap (NOLOAD) : ALIGN(0x1000)
+    {
+        __heap_start = .;
+        . += 4M;
+        __heap_end = .;
+    } :data
+
+    __global_pointer$ = MIN(__bss_start + 0x800, MAX(__data_start + 0x800, __bss_end - 0x800));
+
+    /DISCARD/ :
+    {
+        *(.eh_frame .eh_frame.*)
+        *(.note .note.*)
+    }
+}
